notes.text:
An update is available for java-1.8.0-openjdk.
This update affects Rocky Linux 8.
A Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list
notes.title: Topic

notes.text:
The java-1.8.0-openjdk packages provide the OpenJDK 8 Java Runtime Environment and the OpenJDK 8 Java Software Development Kit.

Security Fix(es):

* JDK: Improve JMX connections (CVE-2026-21925)

* JDK: Improve HttpServer Request handling (CVE-2026-21933)

* JDK: Enhance Certificate Checking (CVE-2026-21945)

* libpng: LIBPNG buffer overflow (CVE-2025-64720)

* libpng: LIBPNG heap buffer overflow (CVE-2025-65018)

Bug Fix(es):

* When using a P11SecretKey for both signing and encryption in FIPS mode, the FIPS PKCS11 provider would fail with a CKR_ATTRIBUTE_VALUE_INVALID error. This was due to the default configuration not applying the CKA_ENCRYPT=true attribute to the key.  The configuration in this release is updated to include this attribute. (Rocky Linux-142865, Rocky Linux-142866, Rocky Linux-142867, Rocky Linux-142868, Rocky Linux-142869, Rocky Linux-142870, Rocky Linux-142871, Rocky Linux-142872, Rocky Linux-142873, Rocky Linux-142874)

For more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.

This advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.
